parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door hinges can cause the door to sag, fall off, or not latch properly, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: The door sags or falls off
the door does not shut properly
the door comes off its hinges
the door latch does not engage
the door opens while driving
the door has a stress fracture or crack around the hinge area.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The weakness of the door frame can cause the door to sag, fall off, or not latch properly, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: The door sags or falls off
the door does not shut properly
the door comes off its hinges
the door latch does not engage
the door opens while driving
the door frame has a stress fracture or crack.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the sliding door can cause the door to come off its tracks, fall off, or not latch properly, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: The sliding door comes off its tracks
the door falls off
the door does not shut properly
the door latch does not engage
the door opens while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The peeling of paint and corrosion on the roof and lift gate can lead to rust and damage to the vehicle's body.
symptoms: Paint peels off
exposing bare metal
corrosion on the roof and lift gate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. In some cases, it can also cause the vehicle to lose control, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle will not shift gears
the transmission makes a clanking or grinding noise
the transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle loses power
the vehicle stalls
the transmission fails to engage from a stop
harsh shifting
inability to shift into reverse.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Component Failure (Differential Pin, Bell Housing, etc.)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of transmission components can cause the transmission to fail, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The differential pin breaks
the bell housing cracks
metal shavings are found in the transmission pan
major gear parts are missing.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of transmission seals can cause the transmission to leak, leading to premature wear and eventual failure.
symptoms: Transmission seal malfunction
metal shavings are found in the transmission pan.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS can lead to extended stopping distances, increased risk of accidents, and potential loss of control, especially in emergency braking situations.
symptoms: The vehicle takes an abnormally long distance to stop
the brakes malfunction
a noise is heard when applying the brakes
the ABS light illuminates on the dashboard.
